<subSubSection id="37D66576E22BFF8FC8DCFEA7FB2AB080" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7F7336FDE22BFF8FC8DCFEA7FB2AB080" blockId="1.[151,1437,367,1594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="4DB8EAEFE22BFF8FC8DCFEA7FEF6B3C3" bold="true" box="[151,279,367,393]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small-sized, brownish delphacids. Head longer and narrower than pronotum (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FCCFCFEB8FB1CB3C0" box="[1207,1277,368,394]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FCCA4FEB8FB1CB3C0" box="[1263,1277,368,394]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Vertex longer than wide at base, anterior margin of vertex rounded projecting in front of eyes (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FCC26FE50FB51B3F8" box="[1133,1200,408,434]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FCCE8FE50FB51B3F8" box="[1187,1200,408,434]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), in profile meeting frons at nearly right angle (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FC992FE08FDC0B390" box="[473,545,448,474]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FCA5AFE08FDC0B390" box="[529,545,448,474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Y-shaped carina with stem absent, submedian carinae uniting before apex of vertex (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FC95AFE20FEB7B048" box="[273,342,488,514]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FC903FE20FEB7B048" box="[328,342,488,514]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Median carinae of frons simple (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FCABBFE20FCD8B048" box="[752,825,488,514]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FCB6CFE20FCD8B048" box="[807,825,488,514]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Lateral carinae of pronotum attaining hind margin (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FC8D4FDD8FF09B060" box="[159,232,528,554]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FC891FDD8FF09B060" box="[218,232,528,554]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Calcar foliate, tectiform, with many black-tipped teeth on lateral margin. Male pygofer with diaphragm narrow, dorsal margin produced medially, truncate or emarginate dorsally (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FCC28FDF0FB4BB018" box="[1123,1194,568,594]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FCCD1FDF0FB4BB018" box="[1178,1194,568,594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); dorsolateral apices of pygofer not expanded (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FC98FFDA8FDEDB030" box="[452,524,608,634]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FC9B0FDA8FDEDB030" box="[507,524,608,634]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Parameres broadened distally with convergent apex (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FCCC1FDA8FB00B030" box="[1162,1249,608,634]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FCC8AFDA8FB00B030" box="[1217,1249,608,634]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Suspensorium strap-shaped (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FC975FD40FE76B0E8" box="[318,407,648,674]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number id="C90424DAE22BFF8FC932FD40FE76B0E8" box="[377,407,648,674]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) and fused with aedeagal base on its dorsal side (
<figureCitation id="E7F72A78E22BFF8FCBB6FD40FB4DB0E8" box="[1021,1196,648,674]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Figs 9, 11, 
